    "faq": {
      "type": "bloomli-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Bloomli a hair loss treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>No. Bloomli products are wellness products designed to support healthier-looking hair, stronger-looking strands, and scalp care. They are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent hair loss, alopecia, hormonal conditions, or any disease.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does it take to see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Hair changes take time because hair grows in cycles. Many people think in terms of a 90-day routine because visible changes typically require consistency over several months. Results vary.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why does Bloomli include gummies, capsules, and serum?",
            "answer": "<p>Each format has a different role. Gummies make daily beauty-nutrient support easy. Capsules allow for a more complete vitamin, mineral, and botanical formula. The serum supports topical scalp care as part of the routine.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Should I use all three products?",
            "answer": "<p>Not everyone needs all three. Gummies are the easiest starting point. Capsules are for customers who want more comprehensive daily support. The serum is for customers who want to add a topical scalp ritual.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does third-party testing prove?",
            "answer": "<p>Third-party testing is quality documentation. It can confirm things like label-claim amount, microbial screening, and heavy-metal screening for a tested lot. It is not clinical outcome data and does not mean every person will see the same visible hair results.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I request product documentation?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Product documentation varies by product and lot, but current COA information is available on request through Bloomli support.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
